c l a u d i a  One of my all time favourite blondes! We all know the tale, discovered in the late 80s at a German discotheque, this one time aspiring lawyer would soon explode into the world of fashion, becoming an ICONIC Supermodel! Her Bridget Bardot likeness soon lead to ELLE covers with Gilles Bensimon, and a career defining campaign for Guess? Jeans, shot by Ellen Von Unwerth, two of the bombshell’s earliest cheerleaders. Her work with both photographers, as well as with the late Herb Ritts, soon caught the attention of Karl Largerfeld, whom made her his longtime Chanel muse, and in turn a Superstar! Claudia was hard to miss throughout the 90s, wether staring on covers of magazines, from Vogue to GQ, to Cosmopolitan and Hello!, everyone wanted a piece of the beautiful blonde. A favourite to all of fashions biggest names, Gianni, Patrick Demarchelier, Lindbergh, Valentino, Arthur Elgort, and many more, it’s safe to say Claudia built one of the most impressive portfolios amongst her contemporaries. Adding to that entrepreneurial endeavours, lucrative multimillion dollar contracts with Revlon and L’Oréal, exercise videos, calendars, and a foray into film, she was also one of the hardest working Supermodels of her time. She, like Cindy, was also one of the few that had crossover appeal, managing to juggle both the worlds of fashion and pop culture, and making men ( straight and gay ) weak at the knees! With so many memorable editorials, covers, campaigns and runway moments, this week is going to be tough in editing down some of my favourites from Claudia, but I’ll give it a shot! Recently celebrating her 53rd birthday, this week I celebrate the iconic, real life Barbie!

She, like Cindy, was also one of the few that had crossover appeal, managing to juggle both the worlds of fashion and pop culture, and making men ( straight and gay ) weak at the knees! With so many memorable editorials, covers, campaigns and runway moments, this week is going to be tough in editing down some of my favourites from Claudia, but I’ll give it a shot! Recently celebrating her 53rd birthday, this week I celebrate the iconic, real life Barbie!

"I prefer to SHOCK rather than to BORE through REPITITION" Yves Saint Laurent

Yves Henri Donat Mathieu-Saint-Laurent (1 August 1936 – 1 June 2008), referred to as Yves Saint Laurent (/ˌiːv ˌsæ̃ lɔːˈrɒ̃/, also UK: /- lɒˈ-/, US: /- loʊˈ-/, French:  or YSL, was a French fashion designer who, in 1962, founded his eponymous fashion label. He is regarded as being among the foremost fashion designers of the twentieth century. In 1985, Caroline Milbank wrote, "The most consistently celebrated and influential designer of the past twenty-five years, Yves Saint Laurent can be credited with both spurring the couture's rise from its 1960s ashes and with finally rendering ready-to-wear reputable."

He developed his style to accommodate the changes in fashion during that period. He approached his aesthetic from a different perspective by helping women find confidence by looking both comfortable and elegant at the same time. He is also credited with having introduced the "Le Smoking" tuxedo suit for women and was known for his use of non-European cultural references and of diverse models.
